         I didn't play NwN.  A lot of the stuff you list here I would actually like in a game though.  I am looking at it from a strictly PvP perspective though.  If I want a pretty PvE game I can stick with EQ.<P>- limit the game to 500 players<BR>- Charge $3.50 an hour<P>Sucks, but really doesn't effect gameplay.<P>- No Melee PvP<P>So what?  I want good PvP, I don't care if I do it with a sword, a spell, or fufme.<P>- Monster UI(AI?) = nil<P>From what I understand...  The AI was predictible.  I don't see that as a problem.  I don't want to battle a computer anyways.  If both players are using the understood AI against each other, it becomes strategy.  If you mean UI(User Interface, then I don't care).<P>- pixles you can count on your hand<BR>- 8 players per "square" (aka fight)<P>Sucks, but really doesn't effect gameplay.<P>- No penatlies for death<BR>- No point to winning<P>Knowing the guy you fought was more skilled then you isn't a penalty/reward?  The problem with EQ is when you win, you rarely know you are the more skilled player.  UO seemed to always be about bugs or the latest patch...<P>- No penalties for hacking<P>I agree, this sucks.<P>- No interesting items<P>I don't know what you mean by this.  I also don't know how it would effect gameplay(PvP).<P>- No communication features<P>Communication is good.<P>- No point to the game<P>What's the point to any game?  A game is what you make of it(especially an RP game).  What's the point of UO?  EQ?  Quake 3?<P>- No individuality (all PC's Clc/Mguser)<BR>- No difference in PC's<P>Everyone that wanted to be PvPers were CLAMs.  From what I hear there were plenty of other classes around doing their own thing, but even amongst the CLAMs.  There were KAAOS gods, MECHs, etc.  It just takes a little imagination, is that so bad a requirement for a game?<P>- No MOB's remotely challenging<BR>- No NPC's... just text and a picture<P>MOB's will never be as challenging as a human.  Even if they were, is that as fun as putting your skill up against another person?<P>- DOS baby! Give me DOS!<P>Who cares?<P>- No updates<BR>- No balances<BR>- No patches<BR>- No "developer"<P>So out of that you get a game that doesn't change every week.  What's so bad about that?  If everyone knows what is overpowered, you can adjust your strategy to compensate.  If a new thing is overpowered every week...  Well, we all played UO.<P>- Volenteer staff payed with free toys <BR>- Steve Case<BR>- Busy signals<BR>- No Internet<BR>- and most importantly... SNOWIE the wonder-btch<P>These all suck, but once again don't effect gameplay.<P>"Oh yeah... NwN was absolutely PERFECT wasn't it? And... when you were playing it you never had a complaint, eh?"<P>Were the complaints about the PvP or the shit around the PvP?<P>Benign<P><BR>
